  codename: "Connectome Harmonics — Spectral Graph Theory of Thought"

summary: |
  Applies Spectral Graph Theory to the latent token trajectory of the LLM. 
  By constructing an adjacency matrix from token transitions and computing the 
  normalized graph Laplacian, we can use the Fiedler value (algebraic connectivity) 
  to measure the topological fragmentation of the thought process (e.g., trapped in 
  an RLHF loop vs. creative biological exploration).

